pageContext.claim: “There is another major caravan forming right now in Honduras. And so far -- we're trying to break it up. But so far, it's bigger than anything we've seen.”
pageContext.analysis: Media reports indicate that the new caravan is much smaller than the caravan that Trump drew attention to before the midterm elections. It was reported to be 500 people at the time of these remarks and grew to 1,500 by Jan. 20, compared to the 7,000 people in the caravan in October.
